If you want to convert object to an array, you have the following options:

1) **`Object.values(post.response)`** will give you the values of the object as an array.

2) **`Object.keys(post.response)`** will give you keys of the object as an array.

3) **`Object.entries(post.response)`** will give you an array where each element is an array consisting of the key and value.

So instead you can do this:
```
Object.keys(response).map( heading =&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th scope=&quot;row&quot;&gt;
  &lt;Media className=&quot;align-items-center&quot;&gt;
   &lt;Media&gt;
    &lt;span className=&quot;badge-dot mr-4&quot;&gt;
     {heading}
    &lt;/span&gt;
   &lt;/Media&gt;
  &lt;/Media&gt;
 &lt;/th&gt;
&lt;td scope=&quot;row&quot;&gt;
  &lt;Media className=&quot;align-items-center&quot;&gt;
   &lt;Media&gt;
    &lt;span className=&quot;badge-dot mr-4&quot;&gt;
     {response[heading]}
    &lt;/span&gt;
   &lt;/Media&gt;
  &lt;/Media&gt;
 &lt;/td&gt;
```

This way you can dynamically define the columns based on the object properties and output the respective values.

